description:
Psalm 15 describes those who are welcome in heaven. In the Sermon on the Mount, a parallel passage to Psalm 15, Jesus expounds on the principles of salvation. Here He showed the importance of having the law written on the heart and laid out principles for practical godliness. What is the difference between keeping the law and fulfilling it? The Pharisees kept the law with meticulous correctness. Jesus fulfilled the law. He didn’t come to lower the standard but to raise it. He calls us to fulfill the law in our own lives. But what does that mean?
  
 How many Christians really trust God? How many have the kind of relationship with Jesus that they would be more willing to die than to dishonor Him? The Greek root from which we get the word “witness” is the same as that which gives us martyr. How are these ideas related? How can we learn to trust God with our lives?
  
 What does it mean to fulfill the law in our lives? Discover the important difference between keeping the law and fulfilling it.
